1 5–6B–23.2.
2 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
3 INDICATED.
4 (2) “COMMON AREA” MEANS ANY AREA IN A COOPERATIVE PROJECT
5 IN WHICH MEMBERS HAVE A POSSESSORY INTEREST IN COMMON.
6 (3) (I) “SENSITIVE INFORMATION” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL’S:
7 1. SOCIAL SECURITY CARD OR SOCIAL SECURITY
8 NUMBER;
9 2. INDIVIDUAL TAXPAYER IDENTIFICATION NUMBER;
10 3. BIRTH CERTIFICATE;
11 4. RACIAL OR ETHNIC ORIGIN;
12 5. NATIONAL ORIGIN;
13 6. CITIZENSHIP OR IMMIGRATION STATUS; OR
14 7. RELIGIOUS OR PHILOSOPHICAL BELIEFS.
15 (II) “SENSITIVE INFORMATION” DOES NOT INCLUDE AN
16 INDIVIDUAL’S GOVERNMENT–ISSUED PHOTO IDENTIFICATION, SUCH AS A DRIVER’S
17 LICENSE.
18 (B) A COOPERATIVE HOUSING CORPORATION MAY NOT REQUIRE A MEMBER
19 OR UNIT OCCUPANT, OR THE GUEST OR CHILD OF A MEMBER OR UNIT OCCUPANT,
20 TO PROVIDE SENSITIVE INFORMATION AS A CONDITION FOR ACCESSING OR USING A
21 RECREATIONAL COMMON AREA, SUCH AS A READING LOUNGE, GAME ROOM,
22 PLAYGROUND, OR SWIMMING POOL.
